Brain vasculitis is a rare disease that affects the blood vessels in the brain. The global brain vasculitis market is expected to witness significant growth by 2028. Factors such as the increasing prevalence of autoimmune disorders, advancements in diagnostic techniques, and a growing geriatric population prone to such conditions are driving the market's expansion. The primary angiitis of the central nervous system (PACNS) segment is anticipated to hold a substantial market share due to the rising incidence of this type of vasculitis. Secondary vasculitis is also expected to contribute significantly to market revenue. In terms of diagnosis, the use of imaging techniques and biopsy procedures will continue to be crucial in accurately identifying brain vasculitis cases. The market players are focusing on developing innovative treatment options to improve patient outcomes.

