Diagnosis plays a crucial role in the effective management of brain vasculitis. Imaging techniques and biopsy procedures remain vital in accurately diagnosing and monitoring the disease progression. The continuous evolution of diagnostic methods will further enhance the early detection and timely intervention in brain vasculitis cases. In the treatment segment, various options such as steroids, immunosuppressants, plasma exchange, monoclonal antibodies, and other emerging therapies are utilized to manage brain vasculitis. The emphasis on developing innovative treatment modalities by key market players underscores the drive towards improving patient outcomes and quality of life.

